To get the Google Client ID and Client Secret, follow these steps:

Step 1: Open Google Cloud Console

Google Cloud Console

Step 2: Create a New Project
Click Select Project → New Project
Enter a project name (e.g., OAuthDemo)
Click Create
Step 3: Enable Google OAuth API
Go to APIs & Services → Library
Search for Google People API
Click Enable
Step 4: Configure OAuth Consent Screen
Go to APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen
Select External
Click Create
Fill in:
App Name
User Support Email
Developer Contact Email
Save and Continue

For classroom demo purposes, you can keep most fields at their defaults.

Step 5: Create OAuth Credentials
Go to APIs & Services → Credentials
Click Create Credentials
Select OAuth Client ID
Choose Web Application
Step 6: Add Redirect URI

Add:http://localhost:8080/login/oauth2/code/google
Step 7: Copy Client ID and Secret

http://localhost:8080/login/oauth2/code/google

Click Create.
